ğŸ§© Technologies Used
ğŸ Python 3
ğŸŒ Requests (for fetching HTML content)
ğŸœ BeautifulSoup (bs4) (for parsing and extracting data)
ğŸ“Š CSV module (for saving data)

ğŸ’» Python Code
import requests
from bs4 import BeautifulSoup
import csv

URL = "https://books.toscrape.com/catalogue/page-1.html"
response = requests.get(URL)
response.raise_for_status()  # check for request errors
soup = BeautifulSoup(response.text, 'html.parser')

products = soup.find_all('article', class_='product_pod')

with open('products.csv', 'w', newline='', encoding='utf-8') as file:
    writer = csv.writer(file)
    writer.writerow(["Product Name", "Price", "Rating"])

    for product in products:
        name = product.h3.a['title']
        price = product.find('p', class_='price_color').text
        rating = product.p['class'][1]  # rating class (e.g., "Three", "Five")
        
        writer.writerow([name, price, rating])

print("âœ… Data saved successfully to 'products.csv'").

